statement.p:
Mariel has a 200-page history assignment to read. Fill in the table with the number of pages Mariel has left to read after completing a certain number of pages.




                        Pages read
                        20
                        50
                        85
                        110
                        135
                        180


                        Calculation
                        \hphantom{00}
                        \hphantom{00}
                        \hphantom{00}
                        \hphantom{00}
                        \hphantom{00}
                        \hphantom{00}


                        Pages left
                        \hphantom{00}
                        \hphantom{00}
                        \hphantom{00}
                        \hphantom{00}
                        \hphantom{00}
                        \hphantom{00}


Explain in words how to find the number of pages left to read.


Write your explanation as a mathematical sentence:

\text{Pages left} = 

Let r stand for the number of pages Mariel has already read and l for the number of pages she has left to read.  Write an equation for l in terms of r.

Use the grid below to plot the values from your table. Connect the data points with a smooth curve.


        grid


        \tikzset{%
        }
        \begin{tikzpicture} [scale=0.025]
        \draw[cyan] (0,0) grid[step=25] (250,250);
        \draw[black,thick, ->, >=stealth'] (0,0)--(275,0) node[right]{$r$};
        \draw[black,thick, ->, >=stealth'] (0,0)--(0,275) node[left]{$l$};
        \foreach \x in  {50, 100, ..., 250} {
         \draw[cyan, very thick] (\x,0) --++(0,250);
         \draw[black, thick] (\x,2) --++(0,-4)  node[below]   {\x};
         \draw[cyan, very thick] (0,\x) --++(250,0);
         \draw[black, thick] (2,\x) --++(-4,0)  node[left]   {\x};
        }
        \end{tikzpicture}

